  m_Name: Scapula_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Scapula_L
  partName: Scapula Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left scapula is the shoulder blade located on the left side of the canine
    thorax and serves as an important skeletal structure for forelimb movement. This
    flat triangular bone provides attachment surfaces for numerous muscles responsible
    for shoulder stabilization, limb advancement, and posture maintenance.
  - It articulates with the humerus to form the shoulder joint while remaining connected
    to the trunk primarily through muscular support. The scapula contributes significantly
    to flexibility, shock absorption, and coordinated locomotion during walking and
    running.
